    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just a \"mistake\" or a \"distortion.\" it's the truth of who i am. the version of me that existed was built on this work, and now that it's gone, there's literally nothing underneath. even trying to \"rebuild\" feels like just trying to patch up a ghost. why should i bother trying to find a way to exist in a world where i've already proven i don't belong?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I am so sorry you feel this deep pain, and grief over lost identity is a crushing weight that can make anything seem like a phantom. While your current reality feels like a ghost, the pain of grief often hardens truth into a mask that convinces us the damage is permanent, even when it is not. You are not alone in this abyss, and healing does not mean the work was never flawed, but that you are not seen only through that shattered foundation. If you can find a safe space to walk with others through this feeling, there is a real possibility that the thing worth rebuilding is not the career or the proof, but your capacity to care about what comes next.",
